then and better equip ourselves for these intense battles in which we feed on. <br><br>In the spirit of competition and sportsmanship I would like to invite all rogues to take part in a fine steel only tournament. A chance to feel that rush, a chance to test the skills you have developed, prove yourself, a chance to learn, a chance to kill, and the bonus of dying a whole lot. <br><br>The tournament will take place in the Arena adjacent to Lake Rathetear on Sunday April 21th. Tournaments like this generally take a good chunk of time, so it will begin early at around 12 noon Central time (1eastern, 11mountain, 10pacific) <br><br>All rogues are welcome, regardless of race, height, guild affiliation, intelligence, personallity, odor.... you get the idea. Inside the arena, all qualms, issues, and rivalries(excepting good natured ones) will be left at the door, and your weapons upon the cold hard ground leaving only pure competition. Invite any rogue you see... any rogue you kill or kills you, any rogue you see running around gfay auction to buy a Stiletto of the Bloodclaw or a fungi tunic. Competition is what makes the world go round. <br><br><br>____________________________________ <br>Rules: <br>1. The 2 competitors will be killed prior to their bout, and escorted from bind point to the ring to minimize the chance of cheating(you know how we rogues are.) Bind points should optimally be right at the arch leading into the PVP area(not the zone tunnel). <br><br>2. Poisons are obviously not going to be an option as the competitors are lead to ring directly from bind point. To remedy this the opponents will hand their poison of choice to an official before being sent to bind point, and will have the poison returned along with his/her choice of fine steel weapons. <br><br>3. Only fine steel weapons will be used, and will be provided by officials. Hopefully we will have a selection of rapier, short spear, and shortsword for those that prefer 1hs offhand. <br><br>4. 20 shurikens will be handed to each rogue before the bout. (For those rogues that choose the archery path(such as myself ), we can either find a basic bow and provide 20 basic arrows, or say too bad... infoplz) <br><br>5. Hiding will be allowed, but only for a very brief period. This will be monitored by an official who will begin binding wound as a competitor begins hiding. (or begin a count of a yet to be determined number) If the official finishes the bind wound measure (or the count) before the hidden rogue reappears, a warning will be announced. 2nd infraction will justify disqualification. <br>{This rule is currently pending change due to no bandages being allotted to the contestants.}<br><br>6. Quite obviously there are to be no buffs on the competing rogues. No SoW, no see invis, no BUFFS. Simple really. <br><br>7. All fights will be to the death. <br><br>8. I reserve the right to add new rules as i see just and as the need arises. <br><br>________________________________________ <br>Bracketing issues <br><br>I will keep track of the tournaments with brackets. <br><br>Entry fees: <br>10pp 1-19 <br>20pp 20-34 <br>30pp 35-44 <br>40pp 45-60 <br><br>Fees will go directly back to the winner of the bracket, or in the case of a tie (in a round robin) it will be distributed evenly to the winners. No money withheld for the Vorren Further Twinkage Foundation Fund... i swear it! Please find some way to have your money there before you bracket begins... or at least finishes. I don't want people wondering where the rest of their lewts went and wondering if I'm maybe keeping it for myself and saving for my fungi.... Have your money, or have someone spot you(not me) its quite simple. <br><br>We can bring in a pre-6 cash handler to manage the fees and payouts. (need a trusty volunteer here ) <br><br>Level classes will be as follows: <br>1-9 <br>10-14 <br>15-19 <br>20-24 <br>25-29 <br>30-34 <br>35-39 <br>40-44 <br>45-49 <br>50-54 <br>55-60 <br><br>Depending on number of rogues in a particular level class, the brackets will be 3 or 4 man round robins, 8 man single elimination tournament, or OMF!!! 16 man single elimination tournament. <br><br>Depending on turnout, additional bouts will be fought to both sides of the platform to increase the number of matches and the speed of the tournament. Each match will have at LEAST one referee overseeing. <br><br><br>Vorren Shadowravyn&quot;<br><br>We apologize for the late notice, but could not possibly hold such an event without our friends The Shanks being aware of the proceedings. Keep in mind this is open to ALL rogues, so bring any friends/enemies/others that you'd like to demolish. ALL rogues, but ONLY rogues, as is our style.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urikkerstronsgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rikkers Tronsgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Patron</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 7:14:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=919.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.everlore.com/gimages/c_rogue.gif width=77 height=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Return of the OBR fine steel tournament</span><hr size=1> You can count on me attending, I haven't been to an Order of the Black Rose event in a <B><I>very</I></B> long time.   <p><center><img src=http://tronsgaard.0catch.com/images/Rikkers_Profile.gif><center> <span style="width: 28%; font-size: 16px; font-family: Comic Sans MS; color: black; Filter: Blur(Add = 1, Direction = 300, Strength = 10)">Rikkers Tronsgaard of Clan Tronsgaard</center></span><BR><center><span style="width: 28%; font-size: 16px; font-family: Comic Sans MS; color: black; Filter: Blur(Add = 1, Direction = 300, Strength = 10)">Circle of U